CalTrak is a full‑stack calorie tracking and nutrition management application. Users can register/login, set personalized fitness 
goals, log foods (via USDA API or manual entry), track daily intake, view progress charts, explore healthy recipes via Spoonacular, 
and manage account settings

## Requirements:
Node.js ≥ 14
npm
MongoDB Atlas account or local MongoDB

## Installation:
npm install

MONGO_URI=your-mongodb-uri
JWT_SECRET=your_jwt_secret   # To create and configure

npm start

## Structure;
CalTrak/
├── public/     # Front‐end HTML, CSS, JS files
│   ├── index.html
│   ├── login.html
│   ├── register.html
│   ├── dashboard.html
│   ├── setgoals.html
│   ├── calories.html
│   ├── progress.html
│   ├── recipes.html
│   ├── settings.html
│   └── *.js, *.css
├── models/     # Mongoose schemas (User, FoodEntry)
│   ├── user.js
│   └── FoodEntry.js
